news.title: Maharashtra government approves conversion of 2.1 lakh sq metres of leasehold land into ownership for Maha Metro
news.para: A senior state government official said the land, previously leased to Maha Metro for 30 years, will now be transferred without conditions on an ownership basis.

news.title: Uttar Pradesh government acquires 13,500 acres of land for new industrial city under BIDA
news.para: The official said the industrial city in Bundelkhand was an effort by the govt to strengthen region's economic foundations.

news.title: Compensation for land acquisition must be guided by equality, equity, justice: SC
news.para: The bench observed the acquisition proceedings commenced in April 2008 and the public purpose of the acquisition was to build Chaudhary Devi Lal Industrial Model Township.

news.title: Andhra Pradesh HC issues notices to state government on land allotment to LuLu Group
news.para: In another PIL filed by YSRCP MLA Lella Appi Reddy, challenging the issuance of NCDs to raise funds, the high court observed that it is a policy decision of the govt.

news.title: Jharkhand HC orders state government to mention timeframe for land survey
news.para: The court was hearing a PIL filed by Gokul Chand. Land survey had started in 1975, prior to bifurcation of the state.

news.title: TCS leases over one million sq ft of office space in Hyderabad
news.para: The lease spans all 19 floors of the building, from ground to the 18th floor, at a monthly rent of Rs 43 per sq. ft., totalling around Rs 4.37 crore per month.

news.title: Kolkata civic body bans future constructions on terraces and basements: Mayor
news.para: KMC consulted the civic legal department on the issue after four rooftop restaurants and lounge bars filed two separate petitions in Calcutta High Court.

news.title: Noida authority plans drone survey to tackle illegal constructions on floodplains
news.para: At a meeting chaired by Noida Authority CEO Lokesh M, a slew of measures was announced to tackle illegal farmhouses and unauthorised constructions mushrooming in the Hindon-Yamuna floodplains.

news.title: Sebi revises REIT, InvIT disclosure guidelines for offer documents
news.para: Sebi also specified additional disclosures, which will be included as a part of the audited financial information and shall also be subjected to audit.

news.title: Nexus Select Trust buys MBD complex in Ludhiana for ₹531 crore
news.para: This high-quality, Grade-A urban consumption centre spans about 0.3 million (3 lakh) square feet and includes a 96-key Radisson Hotel.

news.title: Bombay HC grants interim relief to petitioners in GST dispute on JDAs
news.para: In a case that could have wider implications for the real estate landscape across India, a group of landowners had approached the court to challenge the levy of GST on development rights transferred under such agreements.

news.title: Noida authority initiates recovery of ₹277 crore dues from Sikka Infrastructure
news.para: Noida Authority CEO Lokesh M said the company lost its eligibility for benefits under the state govt's policy announced in Dec 2023 to help stalled real estate projects.

news.title: Germany's Vonovia to swap out CEO, pretax profit up 15% in Q1 2025
news.para: VONOVIA-RESULTS/CEO (UPDATE 3, PIX)UPDATE 3-Vonovia to swap out CEO as it recovers from German property slump

news.title: Kamdhenu's net profit grows 2% to ₹17 crore in Q4 FY25
news.para: Kamdhenu's revenue from operations increased 12 per cent to Rs 197.8 crore in the fourth quarter from Rs 176 crore in the same period a year ago.

news.title: Bengaluru civic body collects ₹1,417 crore in property tax in April 2025
news.para: An official noted that BBMP has set an ambitious target of Rs 5,716 crore for property tax collection this year. With Rs 1,417 crore already collected, the civic body has achieved nearly 25% of its annual goal.

news.title: A new era for mortgage financing
news.para: Mortgage-backed securities (MBS) offer a promising solution. By pooling numerous loans and slicing them into tradable, bond-like securities, intermediaries, such as investment banks, can revitalize the mortgage market

news.title: Ajay Devgn lease out office space in Mumbai for ₹5.47 lakh per month
news.para: The rental agreement spans five years from May 2025 to April 2030, inclusive of an initial fit-out period. The office unit has a carpet area of 2,545 sq ft (236 sq meters).

news.title: Flipspaces raises $35 million
news.para: The capital raised will be used to accelerate growth of Flipspaces across India, U.S. and UAE, strengthen technology and brand leadership, and explore inorganic growth opportunities in new geographies and adjacent categories.

news.title: Lucknow development body to start safety, structural audit of its ageing buildings
news.para: The move comes in the wake of the tragic incident in Transport Nagar last year, prompting authorities to include safety audits as a key component in the updated regulations.

news.title: About 50 acres of land allocated for IT project in Amaravati
news.para: Meanwhile, TCS will be key partner of the project which is considered to be the biggest quantum computer centre in India. The quantum valley project has been planned to be launched by January, 2026.
